org.alljoyn.bus

Class VariantTypeReference<T>

  • Object
    • VariantTypeReference<T>

  • public abstract class VariantTypeReference<T>
extends Object
    Used when calling Variant.getObject(Class) where the wrapped object is a generic type such as Map<K, V>. For example, the proper syntax is getObject(new VariantTypeReference<TreeMap<String, String>>() {}) when the wrapped object is a TreeMap<String, String>.
